conditional statement:
to make set of instructions excecute only when given condition is true
Block of code:
set of instructions
it will be excuted only when that specific condition is true

>condition:An expression that evaluates an result (true or false)

ex:console.log(5>6)

 if:only one possible condition
when condition is true it will be executed else skip

syntax:
if-condition

<script>
      let a = 11;
      let b = 10;
      //5<10
      if (b > a) {
        document.write("hi cse", "<br>");
      }
      document.write("mru");
    </script>
